http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Hyderabad/Rashtrapati-Nilayam-is-open-for-public/article13977642.ece

The Rashtrapati Nilayam gardens will be open for general public from January 3 to 10, from 10 a.m. to 5 p.m. The premises include landscaped gardens, herbal gardens, seasonal flowering plants, and a display of potted plants around the building. According to a press release here on Saturday, the herbal garden has 116 species of medicinal and aromatic plants like sarpgandha, sandalwood, tuber rose, lemon grass etc. The Nakshatra Vatika, inaugurated by the President of India last year, includes 48 trees/plants.